ay 12','',0,5000,0,1,NULL,NULL,0,1661,21742,NULL,0),(44200,1311,'Punisher Khanid SKIN (Permanent)','',0,0.01,0,1,4,NULL,1,2002,NULL,NULL,0),(44201,1311,'Incursus test fix','',0,0.01,0,1,8,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(44202,1311,'Rifter test fix','',0,0.01,0,1,2,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(44203,1311,'Merlin Sukuuvestaa SKIN (Permanent)','',0,0.01,0,1,1,NULL,1,2003,NULL,NULL,0),(44204,943,'300 Aurum Token','This item can be redeemed for 300 Aurum (AUR).<br><br><font color=\"yellow\">To Redeem:</font> Right-click the Aurum Token and select \"Redeem for AUR\".<br><br><font color=\"yellow\">On the Aurum Token:</font> Originally designed for Noble Appliances in YC 113, the aurum token is a physical chit that can be redeemed for a predefined amount of AUR currency.<br><br>Though at first blush it appears to be a large coin, the aurum token shares more in common with high-security datacores. At the center of the token is digital ID paired with a series of suspended entangled electrons. When the token is redeemed, the entangled electrons are engaged, altering their partners located at an off-site bank. Not only does this ensure the exchange occurs instantly, but when combined with a proprietary security shell it renders attempts to tamper or counterfeit the token useless.<br><br>Though the gold and silver case is merely an aesthetic addition, the coin-like appearance has become synonymous with the device, leading to nicknames of \"gold aurum\", or \"golden token\".<br><i>Source: SCOPE fluff piece (unprinted)</i>',0,0.01,0,1,NULL,NULL,1,1427,10831,NULL,0),(44205,1194,'Jezajas Giant Secure Container','From the outside, nothing seems particularly unique about this giant secure container, other than the fact it is sealed with a custom designed electromagnetic bio-lock. It would appear that this container would be impossible to open, if it was not already unlocked. It contains thousands of datacores packed with opinion pieces and news articles on events in New Eden.',10,3,0,1,4,NULL,1,1661,1171,NULL,0),(44206,1194,'A Letter Of Complaint','This formal letter of complaint seems to be addressed to a capsuleer by the name of Grath Telkin, and is written by an unidentified but clearly irate gentleman who appears to have lost a Chimera class carrier in the region of Pure Blind.',10,3,0,1,4,NULL,1,1661,21060,NULL,0),(44207,1194,'Kor-Azor Family Decree','Ratified by Lady Ersilia Kor-Azor, heir of House Kor-Azor, this decree strips capsuleer pilot Lysus of all titles in the Amarr Empire, nullifying his claim to any estate or assets on Eclipticum, in the Imperial system of Kor-Azor Prime. It also publicly denounces his behavior during celebrations of the Coronation of Empress Catiz I, and formally severs any ties with him on behalf of the Kor-Azor family.',10,3,0,1,4,NULL,1,1661,2908,NULL,0),(44208,1194,'Forged Frigate Blueprints','Stored on a single datacore, this data pack contains a blueprint for every standard service frigate. It would appear that these blueprints have been illegally copied, and while they cannot be read by manufacturing equipment in order to be manufactured from, they do appear to have been heavily annotated with the scribblings of a madman.',10,3,0,1,4,NULL,1,1661,2853,NULL,0),(44209,1194,'[CNS] Kiirasha Final Broadcast Fragment','>>> BREAK  CPD AUTH 66401\r\n>>> FTL/FR  30045340\r\n>>> TS/REF  DISTRESS  UNAUTHORIZED AIRLOCK ACCESS\r\n>>> STATUS:\r\nPARTIAL ATMOSPHERE CONTAINEMENT FAILURE\r\nREACTOR CONTAINMENT FAILURE\r\nPROPULSION OFFLINE\r\nCAPACITOR BUSBAR SYSTEM OFFLINE\r\nFTL HARMONIZATION COILS OFFLINE',10,3,0,1,4,NULL,1,1661,2038,NULL,0),(44210,1194,'Scale Model Of [RFS] Mahtu Rea','This is a scale model of the only Matari vessel from the Battle of Mekhios known to survive to this day, which is preserved as a monument to Matari strength and defiance. The real vessel is berthed in Hek VII - Tribal Liberation Force Logistic Support after managing to limp back across the Amarr-Matari border and make port, and is preserved as a monument to the Elder Fleet invasion of the Empire during YC110, which saw countless Matari slaves liberated and evacuated from Imperial space.',10,3,0,1,4,NULL,1,1661,2106,NULL,0),(44211,1194,'Rejected Ship Replacement Program Request','This request for the replacement of a lost Caracal class cruiser bears a large red Rejected stamp. The reasoning given for the rejection was the failure to indicate the pilots preferred flavor of ice cream.',10,3,0,1,4,NULL,1,1661,21060,NULL,0),(44212,1194,'Upwell Consortium Propaganda Reel','This collection of holovids is loaded onto a single reel for convenience, and shows a utopian future on board various classes of citadels and engineering complexes which probably would have existed if capsuleers had not been involved in their construction and destruction for that matter.',10,3,0,1,4,NULL,1,1661,1177,NULL,0),(44213,1194,'The Champion Ship','In response to claims that the Friend Ship is the best ship in New Eden, the Independent Gaming Commission released this model of a Marshal class CONCORD battleship to affirm the position of the Championship as the best ship in New Eden.',10,3,0,1,4,NULL,1,1661,2106,NULL,0),(44214,1194,'CONCORD Speeding Ticket','This speeding ticket was issued by the Directive Enforcement Department to the pilot of a Charon class freighter who was apparently detected travelling at 402,110 m/sec on approach to the Perimeter stargate in the market hub system of Jita. The angry, handwritten response from the capsuleer is undecipherable save for several expletives it would not be appropriate to mention here, and mention of a Machariel class battleship.',10,3,0,1,4,NULL,1,1661,2552,NULL,0),(44215,1194,'Kaalakiota Peaks Vodka','Usually found on the open market in highly decorated bottles rather than these massive distillation tanks, Kaalakiota Peaks Vodka is made with natural spring water filtered through the volcanic rock of the northern peaks of the mountain range from which it takes its name. This particular container is marked with the shipping number of part of an enormous batch worth more than ten billion kredits that went missing after a Guristas attack in Ikoskio that occurred in November YC117.',10,3,0,1,4,NULL,1,1661,1162,NULL,0),(44216,1194,'Armor Plating From TES Seraph','While the Imperial authorities have attempted to prevent looters from taking materials away from the wreckage site of TES Seraph, the Avatar class titan which was destroyed in Safizon, claiming the life of the late Empress of the Amarr Empire, scavengers and black market dealers have managed to make off with more than a few souvenirs. Be careful when transporting this in the Amarr Empire, as the Navy to not take kindly to looters.',10,3,0,1,4,NULL,1,1661,21062,NULL,0),(44217,303,'YC119 Yoiul Festival Accelerator','Cerebral accelerators are military grade boosters that significantly increase a pilots skill development for a given window of time. This is achieved by priming the users brain and neural pathways for increased data bandwidth during knowledge transfer.<br>\nCapsuleers using this accelerator can expect a massive increase in neural bandwidth, aiding much more rapid transfer of neural data from skill packs.<br>\nThe only drawback to this accelerator is that capsuleer training renders it ineffective after one use. It will cease to function after 24 hours once activated, due to natural degradation of the biochemical compounds used to stimulate the users neural activity.\n\nThe compounds are only guaranteed to function until YC119/01/20.',1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL,1,977,10144,NULL,0),(44218,1311,'Stratios SOE Fire Cell (Defense) SKIN (Permanent)','',0,0.01,0,1,8,NULL,1,2030,NULL,NULL,0),(44219,1311,'Astero SOE Fire Cell (Defense) SKIN (Permanent)','',0,0.01,0,1,8,NULL,1,2031,NULL,NULL,0),(44220,1311,'Nestor SOE Fire Cell (Defense) SKIN (Permanent)','',0,0.01,0,1,8,NULL,1,1963,NULL,NULL,0),(44229,1311,'Echo Red Kite SKIN (Permanent)','',0,0.01,0,1,2,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(44230,1311,'Dramiel Red K